CLI test for `ctx_cage::lifecycle::load_cagevars` verifying the precedence rule: process environment variables override `.cagevars` file entries, and file entries fill in gaps when the process env is unset. Tests two variable classes: `CTX_CAGE_EXTRA_PATH` (a reserved var that is applied to the process environment when loaded from file) and arbitrary passthrough vars (returned to the caller but never written to the host process environment).

The test helper `tempdir_with_cagevars` uses a static atomic counter to generate unique temporary directories, allowing multiple test runs in parallel without collision. Both test cases clean up their tempdir and remove env vars at the end to avoid polluting subsequent tests.